name: 1-Datasets
content:
CUSTOMER DATASET  

This dataset has mixed data types and formats. Key columns include:  

  • ID: Unique customer identifier.  
  • Age: Contains a numeric value + birthdate (e.g., `0 12/10/2005`).  
  • City: Textual entries (e.g., `Hicohon`, `Zavazaeza`).  
  • Consumer: Boolean (`TRUE`/`FALSE`) indicating consumer status.  
  • Gender: Binary classification (`Male`/`Female`).  
  • Email: Valid email addresses (e.g., `wcough@puce.cu`).  
  • Postal: Inconsistent postal codes (e.g., `ABL317 Y`, `JAH19047 Y`).  
  • YN: Likely yes/no flags (`Y`/`N`).  
  • Date1â€“Date5: Dates in varying formats (e.g., `4/20/2022`, `20.04.22`, `20220420`, `20-Apr-22`).
